# Testing Rules — Harness Engineering

## Core Principles
- All new code must have accompanying tests.
- Tests must be hermetic (no shared state, no external dependencies in unit tests).
- Prefer fast, isolated unit tests.
- Test coverage should be considered in every plan.

## Hard Stops
- Never merge code without passing tests.
- Never disable tests to "make it work".
- Never commit code that breaks existing tests.

## Test Strategy
- Unit tests → fast and isolated
- Integration tests → only when necessary and documented
- End-to-end tests → run on Cloud Agent when heavy

Follow these rules in addition to `harness-engineering.mdc`.